# Example GenMap parameters file for CAncST pipeline.
# One row per genome. Multiple rows per genome are allowed (one per
# parameter set); the pipeline will compute and combine all of them.
#
# Format: organism K E L I percentile flag
#   organism   - genome identifier (matches utils/genomes/<organism>.fasta)
#   K          - k-mer length (auto-rule of thumb: ceil(log4(genome_size)))
#   E          - allowed mismatches in k-mer counting
#   L          - window length (bp)
#   I          - window pitch / interval (bp)
#   percentile - filtering percentile (lower = stricter)
#   flag       - reserved (use 0)
#
# Defaults below come from template/pipeline_config.yaml (E=0, L=300, I=50,
# percentile=42). K=13 is appropriate for ~150-200 Mb Drosophila genomes.
#
# Usage:
#   cp examples/genmap_params.example template/genmap_params.txt
#   # Or omit and let run_pipeline.sh auto-generate via generate_params.py.

GCF_000001215.4 13 0 300 50 42 0
GCF_016746365.2 13 0 300 50 42 0
GCF_016746395.2 13 0 300 50 42 0
